<div id="review_2346658944" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2346658944" />
    <a title="Michael" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32804270-michael"><img alt="Michael" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1564311252p2/32804270.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2346658944?book_show_action=true">Mar 03, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael" href="/user/show/32804270-michael">Michael</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780141188089" href="/book/show/68063.The_Complete_Stories">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32804270-michael?shelf=2019">2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32804270-michael?shelf=recs">recs</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2346658944" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10334445515264745454">A wide-ranging collection of Gothic tales, semi-autobiographical pieces, and satirical adventures, <i>The Complete Stories of Truman Capote</i> spotlights the writer’s versatile range of talent. Whether examining a young traveler’s close encounter with a strange couple or exploring a queer child’s relationship to his prodigal father, Capote consistently incorporated elements of the grotesque, lavish, and bizarre in his short fiction; his prose is as elaborate as his characterization is nuanced, and man</span>
  <span id="freeText10334445515264745454" style="display:none">A wide-ranging collection of Gothic tales, semi-autobiographical pieces, and satirical adventures, <i>The Complete Stories of Truman Capote</i> spotlights the writer’s versatile range of talent. Whether examining a young traveler’s close encounter with a strange couple or exploring a queer child’s relationship to his prodigal father, Capote consistently incorporated elements of the grotesque, lavish, and bizarre in his short fiction; his prose is as elaborate as his characterization is nuanced, and many of his stories take unexpected turns. Few other American authors of his generation matched Capote’s ability to build a strong sense of atmosphere, and his descriptive passages are unparalleled. Many of his stories, save some of the most anthologized, are open ended and resist academic analysis, but the best of his work is thought provoking and emotionally exhilarating. Favorite stories include “Shut a Final Door,” “Tree of Night,” and “One Christmas.”</span>
  <a data-text-id="10334445515264745454" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


